HEADWORD: Oyster-green
<hw>Oys"ter-green`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A green membranous seaweed (<gen>Ulva</gen>) often found growing on
oysters but common on stones, piles, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

